Package com.cloudhopper.mc.generator.api.spi

Schnittstelle DeploymentConfigGenerator

public interface DeploymentConfigGenerator
Service Provider Interface (SPI) for custom deployment configuration generators.

Implementations of this interface participate in the Cloudhopper annotation processing pipeline by generating provider-specific configuration files (e.g. Terraform, SAM, etc.) for annotated function classes.

This interface allows full control over the transformation of annotated Java classes into deployment artifacts, such as:

  • Function configuration (memory, timeout, runtime)
  • API gateway integration metadata
  • Scheduled trigger definitions
  • Shared resources

Implementations should be declared in META-INF/services using standard Java SPI. Supported features should be declared using GeneratorFeatures.

  • Methodendetails

    • supportsGenerator

      boolean supportsGenerator(String provider)
      Checks whether this generator supports the given provider or target ID.
      Parameter:
      provider - the name of the target generator (e.g. "aws-terraform-java21")
      Gibt zurück:
      true if this generator can handle the specified provider

    • generateServerlessFunctionConfiguration

      void generateServerlessFunctionConfiguration(String generatorId, String outputDir, HandlerInfo handlerInfo, ProcessingEnvironment env) throws ConfigGenerationException
      Generates the deployment configuration for a single serverless function.

      Called once per function discovered with a Function annotation.

      Parameter:
      generatorId - the generator ID (as declared in GeneratorFeatures)
      outputDir - the directory where generated files should be written
      handlerInfo - metadata about the discovered function class
      env - the annotation processing environment
      Löst aus:
      ConfigGenerationException - if generation fails

    • generateApiResourceAndIntegration

      void generateApiResourceAndIntegration(String generatorId, String outputDir, HandlerInfo handlerInfo, ApiOperation apiOperation, ProcessingEnvironment env) throws ConfigGenerationException
      Generates API resource definitions and integration logic (e.g., API Gateway routes).

      Called if the function is annotated with ApiOperation.

      Parameter:
      generatorId - the generator ID
      outputDir - the output directory for generated files
      handlerInfo - metadata about the function
      apiOperation - API metadata annotation
      env - the annotation processing environment
      Löst aus:
      ConfigGenerationException - if generation fails

    • generateScheduledTrigger

      void generateScheduledTrigger(String generatorID, String configOutputDir, HandlerInfo handlerInfo, Schedule schedule, ProcessingEnvironment processingEnv)
      Generates configuration for scheduled triggers.

      Called if the function is annotated with Schedule.

      Parameter:
      generatorID - the generator ID
      configOutputDir - output directory for the config
      handlerInfo - function metadata
      schedule - the schedule annotation
      processingEnv - annotation processing context

    • finalizeConfig

      void finalizeConfig(String providerName, String configOutputDir) throws ConfigGenerationException
      Performs any final configuration generation steps after all handlers are processed.

      This may include writing shared files (e.g. backend definitions, resource groups, etc.)

      Parameter:
      providerName - the name of the generator (e.g. "aws-terraform-java21")
      configOutputDir - the output directory for shared files
      Löst aus:
      ConfigGenerationException - if generation fails

      String getGeneratorID()

      Gibt zurück:
